 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alhazredshadowstepper>Alhazred Shadowstepper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#628CBC>(1/9/03 2:53:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: aa</span><hr size=1> Nokel, if you have trouble soloing with CoD  get a snarer friend to help you. Here's how I do it with aeth/alhaz. SInce I twobox, it's easy for me to synchonize spell casts, but I have done this with Jakke too so I know it's not that hard to do with two people. The important things are snare, tash, and keeping your distance from the fight.<br>
<br>
1. Both target a mob that will single pull, at max spell range.<br>
<br>
2. Aeth tashes and Alhaz snares at same time. Not strictly necessary but easy for me to do since I am twoboxing. I can time the tash to land right before the snare and it helps a lot. Aeth will have aggro, but at max range and snared you have time to refresh and land charm before the mob reaches you.<br>
<br>
3. Aeth charms the mob if snared, mezzes if not. The tash helps ensure that if snare doesnt land, mez will. Get snare and then charm on the mob.<br>
<br>
4. Both chars target victim mob and send the pet mob.<br>
<br>
5. When pet is fighting the victim mob, Aeth tashes and Alhaz snares and roots. After the tash Aeth targets his pet. Alhaz nukes once and reroots if needed. You should now have two mobs fighting, both tashed, both snared, one rooted and the other charmed at max spell range. Very highly controlled.<br>
<br>
6.  Aeth watches his charm status. If charm breaks immediately recharm and /assist alhaz and /pet attack. Alhaz keeps the victim mob rooted the same way.  <br>
<br>
7.  Alhaz nukes once, but no more than once if he can help it. The idea is to let the two mobs trade down but the pet just barely wins.<br>
<br>
8. As soon as the victim dies, /pet sit. This keeps the pet at max range. Aeth casts invis and Alhaz starts a big nuke. Invis lands, charm breaks, then the nuke lands and finishes the pet. If pet is still alive, mez and let Alhaz nukes again.<br>
<br>
This lets me kill most mobs with only one nuke from Alhaz. DPS= 2mobs plus one wizard, divided by two chars.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nokel>Nokel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Trade Skills Conductor<BR>Mr. Gnome Power</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#628CBC>(1/9/03 9:54:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: aa</span><hr size=1> Thanks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
