<br>
However, it's likely that you want to hit 65 at some point and are currently focused more on levelling.  If so, then DC is not really a good investment right now.  Verant did go ahead and put in DC mobs in every PoP zone, even the elemental planes, but there's no way these DC pets can tank any PoP mobs.  They're really only there as a way for a clever enchanter to add some good DPS to his group.  They're nice, but not amazing.<br>
<br>
My advice is to hit level 64 and then go full AA (There's no point in hitting 65 yet since the availability of level 65 spells to most people is very low).  Then go for some of the other AA's mentioned previously in this post.  If you're going to solo a lot, go for domination, not DC.  If you get the critical AA's and have some left over, go for DC.<br>
<br>
As far as zone specific DC mobs, just con them.  Any mob which cons green to you in a PoP zone is the DC target usually.  They're also typically smaller than the normal zone mobs.  Some examples:<br>
<br>
PoInnovation - Little clockwork thingie with a buzzsaw arm.<br>
PoStorms - Bear cubs<br>
PoValor - Rusted suits of armor and baby frogs<br>
PoJustice - Just about any top level mob although I find the guards make especially great DC pets.<br>
<br>
Best way to find the DC mob is just to con.  Should con green to you once you pass level 61 or light blue at level 61. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;"><br>
